Interface Predicate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AnnotatedElement, Element, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BinaryPredicate, DifferentFromPredicate, FeaturePredicate, RelationEntityPredicate, SameAsPredicate, TypePredicate, UnaryPredicate
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinaryPredicateImpl, DifferentFromPredicateImpl, FeaturePredicateImpl, PredicateImpl, RelationEntityPredicateImpl, SameAsPredicateImpl, TypePredicateImpl, UnaryPredicateImpl
    public interface Predicate
extends AnnotatedElement
    A representation of the model object 'Predicate'. Predicate is an annotated element that represents an ontology statement to match, when used in a rule's antecedent, or to infer, when used in a rule's consequent.

    The following features are supported:

    • Antecedent Rule
    • Consequent Rule
